# Member Removal & Admin Notification Walkthrough

We have successfully implemented and audited the member removal feature, providing full end-to-end integration from the frontend organizer panel to the backend DB triggers/API, and feeding directly into a newly created Admin Notice & Activity Feed dashboard card.

Here is the architectural overview of the entire feature workflow:

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    actor Organizer
    actor Admin
    participant Frontend
    participant BackendController as FamilyController
    participant DB as H2/PostgreSQL
    
    Organizer->>Frontend: Clicks "Remove Member"
    Frontend->>BackendController: DELETE /api/families/{familyId}/members/{userId}
    BackendController->>DB: Delete from family_members
    BackendController->>DB: Save ActivityLog ("REMOVE_MEMBER")
    BackendController-->>Frontend: HTTP 200 OK
    Frontend-->>Organizer: Success Toast & List Refreshed
    
    Note over Admin, DB: Real-Time Admin Notice Feed
    Admin->>Frontend: Opens Admin Overview
    Frontend->>BackendController: GET /api/admin/activities
    BackendController->>DB: Fetch ActivityLogs
    BackendController-->>Frontend: List of logs (sorted by date desc)
    Frontend-->>Admin: Renders "Notice & Activity Feed"
```

